content: I don't usually rate apps. But, not one of those bs linked through Facebook kind of sharing. You know what I mean. Add and you get 5star  Now as for my review, it is simple enough to use. I really like the premade wish list folder. That is cool. And being able to add your own titles makes things a lot easier too.
Great app.  I can never remember all the movies I've seen when asked.  This app is what I've been looking for.

I tried 3-4 different apps, and this was by far the best overall. Movie searches are great (shows can be a little hit or miss). Love the layout, features, customizations, and Dev is responsive. Looking forward to continued updates!
Great app I use it for DVDs I've seen and what I want to see
Awsome app well done devs
I have tried many movie collection apps... but this the best well worth the price to unlock all the features.
Best way to stay organized
I like everything except the barcode scanner.  It will not focus on any code.
Scanner doesn't work. It's blurry and takes more than 10 minutes to scan one movie. Very upset I paid for this.
replyContent: Usually the barcode scanner needs only a few seconds to scan and to recognize the code. You can try to use the alternative barcode scanner implementation (See into the settings and switch to ZBAR). Please adjust your rating when everything works like expected. If You still have problems don't hesitate to send me a mail.

content: Just what I was looking for! Well worth the cheap price to unlock all features. I've only had it installed a couple of weeks and already a few updates which have greatly improved it. Thanks!
Good Application. ;-) why can't we add several row for languages & subtitles. If done, i will give 5 stars.

I found a workaround to sync my phone and tablet by sending a backup file of the database automatically via dropbox (using dropsync). But everytime I restore a file, I loose the chapters info from my tv shows. Please fix this or enable auto sync feature between devices. Other than that, this is a very good app. Thank you and congratulations on your work
What I really needed was a collection app that added TV series. I have so many and stopped myself from buying more for fear that I would buy what I own. Thanks so much for this!
I love this app and I went through several. Its easy to use. Barcode scanner works well and when it doesn't it's still a quick search to look up movies.
Does what I need. Developer response to question was very fast and helpfull, as result I purchased the unlocked version.

I would like to share our movie collection with my wife. We both have the app but I do not see a way go share it between the both of us. Help!!!!!!                                                        The app owner gave me good advise on how to share info between phones.
replyContent: You can create a backup of your database in the Backup & restore section and transfer it to the another devices and import it there. Please send me a mail wehen you need more informations. A better sync support comes in the future.

content: Have had a couple wishes for the app but in searching the settings, i have found the dev already thought about them and they were there! Awesome! Something i would like is to have another field where i can put in a volume and disk # that can be seen in list view. Maybe it's already there. Dev? 5 stars if it's there or is added! Thanks
So far i like this app very much but so far i can't figure out how to sync my list from my phone to my tablet. Is it possible to do that? This would be a great feature to add if it don't have it.

Very useful. I am just having a small problem adding a couple movies that are a part of a TV series, like The Walking Dead, and Gilmore Girls. I can't add anything that is part of any TV series. It might just be me, but it always says it can't find the movie. Other than that small problem, it's a great app.
replyContent: Please read the description. You can add TV shows only to a list of type "TV shows". All the mentioned series are in the database. Please switch to the TV shows list and search there for the series.

content: Great UI, excellent app. Great way to keep a track of your DVD (movie and TV) collection. Worth getting the paid version as most would have more than 40+ DVD's (the free app's limitation). Great work devs.

I searched for months for a really good app to catalogue all the movies I had and after uninstalling so many dissatisfying ones, I kept and unlocked this one.  It's search capabilities are great, finding nearly every movie I look up and adds them easily (no entering bar codes necessary).  I have it on my tablet at home to scroll through our collection to find something to watch without having to look through our actually collection.  I also have it on my phone so when I'm out buying movies, I can check to see if I already have it so I don't buy the same movie twice.  The only things I'd like to see added is the ability to mark each movie as 'watched' if you've watched it already as well as the ability to rate it on your own device.  Then, when you're looking for something to watch, you'll know if you've already seen it.  And if you're interested in watching something again, you can pick something you already know you liked or use your ratings to advise friends.  All in all, the best movie catalogue app I've found out there.

Great app. Love the link to IMDb for movies - use this to check certificate and read the parent notes to work out if suitable to watch with my son. Would be 5 stars if there was also an IMDb link for TV shows rather than taking you to the channel website.
Cant bulk scan and scan feature never finds movie.

Awesome app!!!!...... suggestions - would be able to mark if it is a "special edition" "uncut"  "2 disc" & so on and maybe able to link movies u buy as as set for eg "star wars" "fast & furious" "Transformers"
The Barcode database is not that big apparently. A lot of my movies are not found using the scanner and have to search for them manually
Does what you need if you have a large movie collection. Covers multi format and does music too but I ain't used that yet. Very fast to add your movie's to the app and detailed.

Good app. Only thing I would suggest is a 'custom' order, with the ability to slide entries up and down the list and around the grid. This would be more useful then using the custom id system, as you have to change all the ID tags if you add an entry to the middle of the list.
replyContent: You can already sort the list by the custom ID. But it is necessary to fill the id for each movie manually after insertion. I dont want to generate the custom id automatically because some people use not only numeric values. It can be also something like 1A, 2C etc.

content: Just brought this. I left a review on the other app.

Was a bit unsure at first as were a lot of other  because only being able to store 40,50 dvd's. But then I unlocked it and became an all new ball game, put on close to 70 dvd's so far and only one it was unable to find, have emailed the makers and awaiting reply ? The dvd that it was unable to find was called WATERBORNE
Got full fearures,, go what all i need
Great job uploaded my full collection, and works perfect. Excellent job.
Paid to unlock today. Well worth the money. added my  whole collection. The movies have ratings, info on movie, And cast. Just amazing.

Well, after paying to have full access to this app, i find that after entering just over 300 of my 900+ dvd collection, when I go to view the list, it renders only a few of the covers both in list format and in tile format, leaving the app in the neverending loop of "loading" on all the icons. This has made the app virtually useless to me.  Will be uninstalling soon.  Seemed too good to be true when first installed on my Samsung tablet.
replyContent: Sorry but you are the only one who has that problem. On all my testing devices with more than 800 entries in a list i haven't such problems. Nobody else reported similar problems. Please ensure that you have enough space left on the SD CARD. The image cache is created on the SD.
